                                        <cell role="num">15,682,100</cell>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <cell>Per Unit, Spares</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">326,405</cell>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <cell>Total Spares</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">9,139,340</cell>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <cell>Unit Program Cost</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">886,480</cell>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <cell>Total Program Cost</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">24,821,440</cell>
                                    </row>
                                </table></p>
                            <p>(3) The grand total program estimated cost for 54 <gloss target="#t_C1">C</gloss>–119G aircraft and support is
                                $48,243,644.</p>
                            <p>(4) An additional month should be added to the delivery schedule
                                indicated above for each month’s delay up to six months in the
                                go-ahead dates.</p>
                            <list>
                                <label>3.</label>
                                <item>This information covers partial pricing and availability on
                                    the aircraft requested by the Indian Government. In view of the
                                    fact that there are no F–84E or F–80B aircraft available for
                                    release to the Indian Government, the Department of the Air
                                    Force is considering the substitution of the F–84F, F–84G or
                                    F–86 aircraft. Information on F–9F aircraft is being held in
                                    abeyance pending a resolution of the entire fighter portion of
                                    the Indian request.</item>
                                <pb facs="0613" n="1663" xml:id="pg_1663"/>
                                <label>4.</label>
                                <item>It is expected that further information covering the remaining
                                    aircraft on this request will be forthcoming approximately 31
                                    August 1952.</item>
                            </list>
